>Magra: AEELNOO H1 LOO.E +15 334
#note this was a supertough and critical play. I played here to take out high scoring plays at 3I and to keep a flexible leave. After simming a lot of different options this rises to the top, dead even with ONLOAD at 2A. ROLE at E4 is quite logical but LOOSE wins on the sim because it has 3 extra points of defense. ONLOAD is the only competitor. It looks crazy because there are so many tiles that go at 1A, but given that my chances of winning are only 1/3 for any play I guess the logic is to turn over tiles and try to draw a big play up at the top-left. When I try adding some plies ONLOAD starts to look worse.
>Bruce_D'Ambrosio: LW 3H .WL +18 358
>Magra: AEIILNT E3 A.IL +18 352
#note I swear that this sim looked a lot different the first time I simmed it. conceptually I kinda ike ILIA because it takes out all the scoring plays at the top-left that will allow bruce to outrun me and maybe makes him work harder. however, on the sim my play looks good but the two best are fishing off LI or playing TI for 10 at 3B, because the bingo percentages rise a lot. I was kinda banking on catching him without having to bingo but on reflection ILIA leaves too few in the  bag and ARIL probably won't catch him anyway. The big mystery to me is why TI is so much better than LI at 3B. any ideas, anyone? the bingo percentage is like 10% higher. I suspect it has to do with bingos on column D. For all that quackle says I really don't like LI at the bottom-left at all because he will go out of his way to block given that I have essentially no other way of winning. TI looks better but I still don't exactly see how it wins games for me.
